From 7976b8ea9094c7c874d335a71f9f5144b9bd8789 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 05:22:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] styles: fix broken comment block causing esbuild
 css-syntax-error warning
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A prior commit ('added new theme color') deleted the opening banner
line of the '/* EXPANDED SIDEBAR — Clinical Depth Design */' comment
but left its closing '*/' in place. Everything between the previous
comment's real end and this stray '*/' (the ocean/sunset/violet
focus-ring rules) was silently swallowed into a comment, and the
dangling '*/' then read as a syntax error to esbuild/CSS parsers.

Restored the missing opening banner line so the comment is
well-formed again. No rule content changed — purely a comment-nesting
fix. Verified: zero /* */ mismatches across styles.css and
'ng build --configuration development' now produces no CSS warnings.
---
 src/styles.css | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/styles.css b/src/styles.css
index 8c49778..2657da4 100644
--- a/src/styles.css
+++ b/src/styles.css
@@ -4485,7 +4485,8 @@
 [data-palette="sunset"]  .field-input:focus { border-color: var(--primary); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--lis-primary-xlight); }
 [data-palette="violet"]  .field-input:focus { border-color: var(--primary); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--lis-primary-xlight); }
 
-
+/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
+   EXPANDED SIDEBAR — Clinical Depth Design
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
 
 /* ── Shell ── */
